According to the article's history, is was contained in rubber. Could have been synthetic rubber.

Then again, synthetic rubber is made from petroleum byproducts. It's a stretch, but you could argue that anything made from petroleum is a biological material, since the oil likely started off as a giant mat of algae, even if it is processed to the point of being incredibly toxic to most biological organisms.





